---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { AUTHOR, SOCIAL } from '../consts';
---
<BaseLayout title="About" description="Explore the world of Artificial Intelligence with Yaima Valdivia.">
  <main class="container about-page">
    <h1 class="page-title">About Me</h1>
    <img class="about__photo" src="/images/profile.webp" alt={AUTHOR} />
    <div class="about-bio">
      <p>Hey! I'm Yaima Valdivia, a software engineer and founder.</p>
      <p>
        I have an MS in Computer Science from Georgia Tech, where I specialized
        in Artificial Intelligence. Since then I've worked on agentic AI and how
        it behaves in the wild, with a focus on keeping systems secure.
      </p>
      <p>
        When I'm not writing code, I'm usually behind a camera.
        <a href={SOCIAL.instagram} target="_blank" rel="noopener">Photography</a>
        keeps me sane.
      </p>
      <p>
        I like to know why things work. So I poke at the edges of what's
        possible, in engineering, in photography, and in late-night conversations
        about consciousness and computation.
      </p>
      <p>
        I write this blog to think out loud about what's happening in tech. No
        gatekeeping, no pretending I have all the answers.
      </p>
      <p>
        Whether you're debugging your first Python script or you've been shipping
        code since dial-up, I hope something here makes you go "huh, hadn't
        thought of it that way."
      </p>
      <p>
        Tech gets more interesting when we work it out together. If AI, computer
        science, cognitive science, or anything nearby is your thing, stick
        around.
      </p>
    </div>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
